        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[New Switch 2 games Splatoon Raiders and Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave age-rated in Europe]]></title>
            <link>https://www.eurogamer.net/switch-2-splatoon-raiders-and-fire-emblem-fortunes-weave-pegi-age-ratings</link>
            <guid>1489321</guid>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div>
      <article data-ads="true" data-article-type="news" data-article-group="news" data-paywalled="false" data-premium="false" data-sponsored="false" data-type="article">


<header data-component="article-header">
  

    


  <p>

  <figure>
      <picture>
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=3&amp;auto=webp" media="(max-width: 549px) and (max-resolution: 3dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.5&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.5dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=1.75&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 1.75dppx)">
        <source srcset="https://assetsio.gnwcdn.com/Splatoon-Raiders_group.png?width=570&amp;quality=85&amp;format=jpg&amp;dpr=2&amp;auto=webp" media="(min-width: 550px) and (max-resolution: 2dppx)">
        
      </picture>

        <figcaption>
          <span>Image credit: <cite>Nintendo</cite></span>
        </figcaption>
  </figure>
  </p>

    

</header>
  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Once <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/tomodachi-life-living-the-dream">Tomodachi Life: Living the Dream</a> and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/yoshi-and-the-mysterious-book">Yoshi and the Mysterious Book</a> are out later this week and next month, Nintendo's first-party roadmap is a bit of a mystery. But now two PEGI age ratings for Europe have offered a clue at what may be coming next.</p>
<p>This last weekend, two high-profile <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/platforms/switch-2">Nintendo Switch 2</a> releases tentatively set for 2026 got their respective age ratings from PEGI (via <a href="https://mynintendonews.com/2026/04/11/splatoon-raiders-rated-by-pegi-suggests-imminent-release/">My Nintendo News</a>), the standard European game age-rating system.</p> <figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Splatoon Raiders - Official Announcement and Splatoon 3 Update Trailer" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/t0LcunUaS80?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Splatoon Raiders - Official Announcement and Splatoon 3 Update Trailer</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/t0LcunUaS80?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/t0LcunUaS80?autoplay=1" title="Splatoon Raiders - Official Announcement and Splatoon 3 Update Trailer">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t0LcunUaS80" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figure>
<p>First, we have <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/splatoon-raiders-announced-for-switch-2-plus-a-chonky-splatoon-3-update-incoming">Splatoon Raiders</a>, the mysterious spin-off of the charming third-person shooter series. It's received a PEGI 7 rating, the same as <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/splatoon-3">Splatoon 3</a>. We've double-checked <a href="https://www.nintendo.com/en-gb/Games/Nintendo-Switch-2-games/Splatoon-Raiders-2846969.html">the Splatoon Raiders age-rating on the European eShop pages</a> and it's the same.</p> <figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave - Official Reveal Trailer | Nintendo Direct" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qV6Csk2RYZk?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave - Official Reveal Trailer | Nintendo Direct</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/qV6Csk2RYZk?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/qV6Csk2RYZk?autoplay=1" title="Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave - Official Reveal Trailer | Nintendo Direct">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qV6Csk2RYZk" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figure>
<p>Then we have <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/nintendo-reveals-new-fire-emblem-game-coming-to-switch-2">Fire Emblem: Fortune's Weave</a>, the next entry in the long-running turn-based strategy series, <a href="https://www.nintendo.com/en-gb/Games/Nintendo-Switch-2-games/Fire-Emblem-Fortune-s-Weave-2915498.html">which has been given a PEGI 12 rating in Europe</a>, like previous Fire Emblem games Three Houses and Engage.</p>
<p>The intriguing thing about both updates is the timing: Nintendo appears to have updated them nearly at the same time. With <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/all-new-star-fox-and-zelda-ocarina-of-time-remake-reportedly-set-for-switch-2-release-this-year">talk of a new Star Fox being real and The Legend of Zelda: Ocarina of Time getting a remake later this year</a>, it's hard not to theorise a that new big Nintendo Direct focusing on the latter half of 2026 could be around the corner.</p>

        </div>

  
      </article>



  



  

  <section>
    <span>Related topics</span>

    
  </section>
  </div></div><br/><br/>https://www.eurogamer.net/switch-2-splatoon-raiders-and-fire-emblem-fortunes-weave-pegi-age-ratings]]></content:encoded>
